Also given; length of wire $Q$ $=25 \mathrm{~cm}=0.25 \mathrm{~m}$
Force on wire $\mathrm{Q}$ due to wire $\mathrm{R}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
&F_{Q R}=10^{-7} \times \frac{2 \times 20 \times 10}{0.05} \times 0.25 \\
&=20 \times 10^{-5} \mathrm{~N} \text { (Towards left) }
\end{aligned}
$$
Force on wire $\mathrm{Q}$ due to wire $\mathrm{P}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
&F_{Q P}=10^{-7} \times \frac{2 \times 30 \times 10}{0.03} \times 0.25 \\
&=50 \times 10^{-5} \mathrm{~N} \text { (Towards right) } \\
&\text { Hence, } F_{\text {net }}=F_{Q P}-F_{Q R} \\
&=50 \times 10^{-5} \mathrm{~N}-20 \times 10^{-5} \mathrm{~N} \\
&=3 \times 10^{-4} \mathrm{~N} \text { towards right }
\end{aligned}
$$
